name: Baked Cajun Swai Fillets
author: Pirate of Fire
summary: A nice, delicate, tender fish fillet with a slight kick! Serve with broccoli almodine rice or assorted veggies!
ingredients: 1 pinch Cajun seasoning, or more to taste
1 pinch cayenne pepper, or more to taste
¼ cup unsalted butter, cut into 4 pieces
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees F (165 degrees C)
Arrange swai fish in a nonstick baking dish; season with Cajun seasoning and cayenne pepper
Layer banana peppers, habanero peppers, and thyme leaves on top of each fish fillet
Place 1 piece butter on top of each fish fillet
Bake in the preheated oven until fish flakes easily with a fork, 30 to 40 minutes
